<subSubSection id="8EDA65667722FFE5F2A2FB36DC626B04" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7722FFE5F2A2FB36DC2E6AC1" blockId="19.[160,1155,1216,1311]" box="[160,285,1216,1242]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">
<emphasis id="F4B4EAFF7722FFE5F2A2FB36DC2E6AC1" bold="true" box="[160,285,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7722FFE5F2A2FB15DC626B04" blockId="19.[160,1155,1216,1311]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">The species name refers to the greyish yellow median abdominal band in the preserved male specimen.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8EDA65667722FFE5F2A2FABDDC766BEB" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7722FFE5F2A2FABDDC276B7E" blockId="19.[160,1156,1355,1520]" box="[160,276,1355,1381]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">
<emphasis id="F4B4EAFF7722FFE5F2A2FABDDC276B7E" bold="true" box="[160,276,1355,1381]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7722FFE5F2A2FA99DC766BEB" blockId="19.[160,1156,1355,1520]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">
The species is distinguishable from other congeners by the greyish pale yellow median band of abdomen (
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687722FFE5F374FA67DCE26BB1" box="[374,465,1425,1450]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(a)), oval bulbus with well-developed posterior lobe, long, thin embolus (
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687722FFE5F311FA42DC4D6BD6" box="[275,382,1460,1485]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figures 8</figureCitation>
(d), 
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687722FFE5F3A8FA42DF276BD6" box="[426,532,1460,1485]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1071,1094]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,143,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-124@19.[166,1149,142,1040]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b), a. Palp, ventral view. (b). retrolateral view. Abbreviations: e = embolus; dcrta = dorsal curve of rta; sd = sperm duct; plt = posterior lobe of tegulum; t = tegulum; vcrta = ventral curve of rta. Scale bars: (a–d) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405259/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figures 9</figureCitation>
(a)), small RTA with a sharpened point (
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687722FFE5F1E1FA42D97D6BD6" box="[995,1102,1460,1485]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figures 8</figureCitation>
(d,e), 
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687722FFE5F2A2FA21DC3B6BEB" box="[160,264,1495,1520]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1071,1094]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,143,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-124@19.[166,1149,142,1040]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b), a. Palp, ventral view. (b). retrolateral view. Abbreviations: e = embolus; dcrta = dorsal curve of rta; sd = sperm duct; plt = posterior lobe of tegulum; t = tegulum; vcrta = ventral curve of rta. Scale bars: (a–d) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405259/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figures 9</figureCitation>
(a,b)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8EDA65667722FFE2F2A2F9EADC426C96" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="2782" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781" type="description">
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7722FFE5F2A2F9EADC15682D" blockId="19.[160,1156,1564,1728]" box="[160,294,1564,1590]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">
<emphasis id="F4B4EAFF7722FFE5F2A2F9EADC15682D" bold="true" box="[160,294,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7722FFE2F2A2F9C9DEBE6EF6" blockId="19.[160,1156,1564,1728]" lastBlockId="20.[160,1156,142,653]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="2782" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">
Male: Medium-sized spider. In ethanol-preserved specimens, prosoma brown and covered with greyish white blotches laterally (
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687722FFE5F03DF994DFA96860" box="[575,666,1634,1659]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(a)). Eye field rather elevated. Fovea distinct. ALEs, PMES and PLEs covered with black rings. Prosoma high, sloping posteriorly. Chelicerae brown, yellowish brown fangs. Sternum oval, yellowish brown centrally, edges brown (
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687725FFE2F344FF78DC956EBC" box="[326,422,142,167]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(b)). Posterior margin of prosoma blackish brown, steep, slightly truncated. Leg I dark brown, rather robust, elongated, dense black bristles on patella, tibia metatarsus I, others brown with yellowish brown banding pattern.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7725FFE2F2C2FF00DED56F81" blockId="20.[160,1156,142,653]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">
Abdomen oval, smaller and narrower than prosoma, tapering posteriorly. Dorsum blackish grey with broad, greyish pale yellow median band dispersed with grey dots (
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687725FFE2F2AAFECADC306F4E" box="[168,259,316,341]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(a)). Ventrum greyish yellow with a dark grey median band comprising four rows of greyish brown dots from epigastric furrow to spinnerets (
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687725FFE2F171FEA8DEE66F6C" box="[883,981,350,375]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(b)). Spinnerets greyish brown. Measurements: TL 5.98, AL 2.86, AW 1.69, PL 3.12, PW 2.34.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7725FFE2F2C2FE52D9276C71" blockId="20.[160,1156,142,653]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">
Yellowish brown palp. Moderately long cymbium with narrowest distal region. Embolus thin, long originating from posterior portion of the bulbus and partially surrounding it (
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687725FFE2F2A5FE1FDC386C19" box="[167,267,489,514]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figures 8</figureCitation>
(d), 
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687725FFE2F333FE1FDCA76C19" box="[305,404,489,514]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1071,1094]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,143,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-124@19.[166,1149,142,1040]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b), a. Palp, ventral view. (b). retrolateral view. Abbreviations: e = embolus; dcrta = dorsal curve of rta; sd = sperm duct; plt = posterior lobe of tegulum; t = tegulum; vcrta = ventral curve of rta. Scale bars: (a–d) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405259/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figures 9</figureCitation>
(a)).Bulbus oval with a large posterior lobe (
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687725FFE2F169FE1FDEFC6C19" box="[875,975,489,514]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figures 8</figureCitation>
(d,e), 
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687725FFE2F605FE1FD9596C19" box="[1031,1130,489,514]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1071,1094]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,143,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-124@19.[166,1149,142,1040]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b), a. Palp, ventral view. (b). retrolateral view. Abbreviations: e = embolus; dcrta = dorsal curve of rta; sd = sperm duct; plt = posterior lobe of tegulum; t = tegulum; vcrta = ventral curve of rta. Scale bars: (a–d) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405259/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figures 9</figureCitation>
(a, b)). Sperm duct comparably broader at the distal end of tegulum, narrower at the posterior bulbus. Palpal tibia comparably short. Short RTA with an upper dorsal curve and a lower ventral curve terminating in a straight pointed tip (
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687725FFE2F0D0FDA7DE0B6C71" box="[722,824,593,618]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figures 8</figureCitation>
(d,e), 
<figureCitation id="5EFB2A687725FFE2F170FDA7DEE46C71" box="[882,983,593,618]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1071,1094]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,143,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-124@19.[166,1149,142,1040]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b), a. Palp, ventral view. (b). retrolateral view. Abbreviations: e = embolus; dcrta = dorsal curve of rta; sd = sperm duct; plt = posterior lobe of tegulum; t = tegulum; vcrta = ventral curve of rta. Scale bars: (a–d) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405259/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figures 9</figureCitation>
(a,b)).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7725FFE2F2A1FD82DC426C96" blockId="20.[160,1156,142,653]" box="[163,369,628,653]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Female: unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8EDA65667725FFE2F2A2FD4EDEAE6A36" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7725FFE2F2A2FD4EDC356CC9" blockId="20.[160,1156,696,1069]" box="[160,262,696,722]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">
<emphasis id="F4B4EAFF7725FFE2F2A2FD4EDC356CC9" bold="true" box="[160,262,696,722]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7725FFE2F2A2FD2AD9546DDE" blockId="20.[160,1156,696,1069]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">
This species is provisionally placed here based on currently available evidence. We do not have the corresponding female or molecular sequence data for this species for a better placement. The male palp suggests that it can be possibly also placed in either 
<taxonomicName id="01C04D6E7725FFE2F60DFCD7D9556D21" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[1039,1126,801,826]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Evarcha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F4B4EAFF7725FFE2F60DFCD7D9556D21" box="[1039,1126,801,826]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Evarcha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="01C04D6E7725FFE2F2A2FCB2DC3A6D46" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[160,265,836,861]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pancorius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F4B4EAFF7725FFE2F2A2FCB2DC3A6D46" box="[160,265,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Pancorius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(not metallic green, but striped, bulb with prominent lobe). However, the origin and shape of the embolus (long thin embolus that starts at about 6:00 o’clock position) are more or less as in 
<taxonomicName id="01C04D6E7725FFE2F39AFC7FDCCA6DB9" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[408,505,905,930]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Colopsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F4B4EAFF7725FFE2F39AFC7FDCCA6DB9" box="[408,505,905,930]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Colopsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the length of the embolus, we predict that the insemination duct of the unknown female could be longer than that of its congeners.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C67F36ED7725FFE2F2C2FC39DEAE6A36" blockId="20.[160,1156,696,1069]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">
During the review process it was suggested that this 
<typeStatus id="197B884F7725FFE2F11EFC39DEB36DF3" box="[796,896,975,1000]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">holotype</typeStatus>
is the male to go with the females of 
<taxonomicName id="01C04D6E7725FFE2F346FC07DCA36A11" authorityName="Kanesharatnam &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2021" box="[324,400,1009,1034]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Evarcha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latus">
<emphasis id="F4B4EAFF7725FFE2F346FC07DCA36A11" box="[324,400,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">E. latus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We note that this issue can only be ratified in a broader population genetic study, which is beyond the scope of the current endeavour.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
